    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>ground</strong> <strong>allspice </strong>and <strong>ground cumin</strong> to the dish with the <strong>white long grain rice</strong>, <strong>drained black beans </strong>and<strong> remaining thyme</strong> (including the stalks!) then add the<strong> chicken stock mix </strong>and the<strong> creamed coconut </strong>to the dish with 300ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and mix everything together</p><p>Season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>then bring to the boil over a high heat, once boiling, cover with a lid and put the dish in the oven for 15-20 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p>",
