    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken has been in the oven for 5 min, cut 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4]</span> pieces of<strong> tin foil</strong> approx. the size of an A3 sheet of paper and layer them over each other</p><p>Add the <strong>spinach</strong> to the middle with a few small knobs of <strong>butter</strong>, a generous grind of <strong>black pepper </strong>and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>water</strong></p><p>Scrunch the edges of the foil around the spinach to form 1 <span class=\"text-danger\">[2] </span>sealed parcel<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> then add to the other side of the baking tray with the chicken for the remaining 5-7 min</p>",
